# Module layout & URL routing

## File locations for module `X`

| Concern | Legacy (`modules/X/`) | Modern (`src/Modules/X/`) |
|---|---|---|
| Controller (View) | `modules/X/views/<View>.php` | `src/Modules/X/Views/<View>.php` |
| Action | `modules/X/actions/<Action>.php` | `src/Modules/X/Actions/<Action>.php` |
| Model | `modules/X/models/<Model>.php` | `src/Modules/X/Models/<Model>.php` |
| Smarty templates | `layouts/basic/modules/X/*.tpl` | same |
| JS/CSS | `public/layouts/basic/modules/X/resources/*.js` | same |
| Language strings | `languages/<lang>/X.php` | same |

## URL â†’ file mapping

- `index.php?module=X&view=V`     â†’ `views/V.php` (or `Views/V.php`)
- `index.php?module=X&action=A`   â†’ `actions/A.php` (typically AJAX/POST)
- `index.php?parent=Settings&module=X&view=V` â†’ `src/Modules/Settings/X/Views/V.php`

## Adding a new view/action

1. Class name = file basename (e.g. `Edit.php` defines `<Module>_Edit_View` or `App\Modules\<Module>\Views\Edit`).
2. Wire the URL with `view=` or `action=` â€” no router config needed.
3. For Settings views, extend `App\Modules\Settings\Base\Views\Index` to inherit the menu.

## Calendar module (common pitfalls)

| Concern | Location |
|---|---|
| FullCalendar UI | `public/layouts/basic/modules/Calendar/resources/CalendarView.js` (+ `.min.js` via `js.mdc`) |
| Load events AJAX | `src/Modules/Calendar/Actions/Calendar.php` â†’ `mode=getEvents` |
| Event payload | `src/Modules/Calendar/Models/Calendar.php` â†’ `getEntity()` |
| Quick-create save | `src/Modules/Calendar/Actions/SaveAjax.php` |
| Quick-create modal submit lock | `public/layouts/basic/modules/Base/resources/Header.js` (`quickCreateSave` reject must `form.removeData('submit')`) |

- **Popover / status labels**: `getEntity()` sets raw `sta` / `state` (picklist codes like `PLL_PLANNED`) and **translated** `labels.sta`, `labels.state`, `labels.pri`. UI must prefer `event.labels.*` (see `getCalendarEventLabel()` in `CalendarView.js`). The calendar page loads only `languages/*/Calendar.json` â†’ `jsLanguageStrings`; `JS_PLL_*` in `Vtiger.json` are not exported there unless duplicated in `Calendar.json`.
- **`event.state`**: `Module::getCalendarState()` returns picklist **values**, not display text â€” never pass `event.state` straight to `app.vtranslate()` expecting a label.
- **Drag-select on month grid**: `selectDays()` â€” use **moment** for start/end; `Date.parse('YYYY-MM-DDTHH:mm')` often returns `NaN` and breaks the quick-create modal.
- **After save**: prefer `loadCalendarData(true)` over only `addCalendarEvent()` (toolbar filter `showType`, missing display fields).
- **Browser test**: MCP browser on `http://localhost`; hard-refresh after JS changes so `CalendarView.js?s=` updates.
